<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>ELECTRICAL SYSTEM TROUBLESHOOTING GUIDE / 5000 9100 9200 9400 9900 MODELS BUILT OCTOBER 1, 1998 AND AFTER -
        GAUGES AND WARNING LIGHTS - 5000, 5000i, 9000, 9000i - REMOVE AND INSTALL - ELECTRIC GAUGES
    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="remove" graphiccount="6">
        <title>ELECTRIC GAUGES</title>
        <svcsubproc id="x0820706">
            <title>Removing Electric Gauges</title>
            <para>All of the electrical (and electronic) gauges can be removed without removing the gauge cluster.
            </para>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Twist the gauge bezel counterclockwise 1/8 turn to unlock (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f0820702">Figure 2</hotlnk>).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Pull the bezel out 1/2 inch.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Grasp bezel and pull straight out. This removes the gauge and the bezel (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f0820703">Figure 3</hotlnk>).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f0820702" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figg08/G0803502.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                         scalefitheight="312px" resolution="72"/>
                <caption>Twist Gauge Bezel Counterclockwise to Unlock</caption>
            </figure>
            <figure id="f0820703" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figg08/G0803503.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                         scalefitheight="312px" resolution="72"/>
                <caption>Grasp Bezel and Pull Straight Out</caption>
            </figure>
        </svcsubproc>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Installing Electrical Gauges</title>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Position bezel over the gauge, with the the top of the bezel aligned to the top of the
                    gauge (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f0820704">Figure 4</hotlnk>). To determine which is the bezel top, the bottom inside
                    edge of the bezel has a small flat area. The word "TOP" is also printed on the top edge of the
                    bezel, although hard to see.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Push the bezel toward the gauge, fitting it to the gauge, then turn the bezel clockwise
                    until the bezel arms fit into the gauge notches (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f0820705">Figure 5</hotlnk>).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Insert the gauge/bezel assembly into the cluster pin receptacles, and push in until it
                    is completely seated (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f0820706">Figure 6</hotlnk>).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Twist the bezel clockwise 1/8 turn to lock (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f0820707">Figure 7</hotlnk>).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f0820704" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figg08/G0803504.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="232px"
                         scalefitheight="312px" resolution="72"/>
                <caption>Position Bezel Over Gauge</caption>
            </figure>
            <figure id="f0820705" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figg08/G0803505.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                         scalefitheight="232px" resolution="72"/>
                <caption>Turn Bezel Clockwise</caption>
            </figure>
            <figure id="f0820706" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figg08/G0803506.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                         scalefitheight="352px" resolution="72"/>
                <caption>Insert Gauge/Bezel Assembly into Cluster Pin Receptacles</caption>
            </figure>
            <figure id="f0820707" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figg08/G0803507.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                         scalefitheight="312px" resolution="72"/>
                <caption>Twist Bezel Clockwise to Lock</caption>
            </figure>
        </svcsubproc>
    </svcproc>
